data.chText: 所属不清的；两可之间的；临界的
data.enText: not clearly belonging to a particular condition or group; not clearly acceptable

data.chText: 在难以定夺的情况下，教师将根据学生先前的作业做出最终评分。
data.enText: In borderline cases teachers will take the final decision, based on the student's previous work.

data.chText: 考试得分刚刚在及格线上 / 下
data.enText: a borderline pass/fail in an exam

data.chText: 两种品质（或状况）之间的分界线
data.enText: the division between two qualities or conditions

data.chText: 这部传记有时混淆了事实和虚构。
data.enText: This biography sometimes crosses the borderline between fact and fiction.

word_means: 两种品质之间的分界线
simple_means.memory_skill: border 边界 + line 直线，线条 → 边界，边缘

means: 两种品质(或状况)之间的分界线

ex.chText: 两年以后，他被派到了中缅边界。
ex.enText: Two years later, he was sent to the border between China and Myanmar.

synonyms.bx: 多指靠近两国或两地区分界线的区域。

ex.enText: the borderline between China and India

synonyms.bx: 指划定国与国之间边界的标志线。

ex.chText: 他们标出了篮球场的边界。
ex.enText: They marked the boundaries of the basketball court.

ex.chText: 这条河构成了我这块地和他那块地之间的分界线。
ex.enText: The river forms the boundary between my land and his.

synonyms.bx: 侧重指某区域最外的界线，常和领土有关，也指地图上正式标定的、双方认可的边界或较小行政单位间的界线。

ex.chText: 中国的边界和越南相接。
ex.enText: China has a frontier with Vietnam.

ex.chText: 战士们守卫边疆，防止外敌入侵。
ex.enText: Soldiers guard the frontier against invasion.

synonyms.bx: 指两国接壤的前沿地区，多有军队驻防。

tr: a line that indicates a boundary

value.def: The borderline between two different or opposite things is the division between them.

example.ex: ...a task which involves exploring the borderline between painting and photography.
example.tran: 一项探究绘画与摄影之间界线的工作

value.tran: （两种不同或相反事物之间的）分界线

value.def: Something that is borderline is only just acceptable as a member of a class or group.

example.ex: Some were obviously unsuitable and could be ruled out at once. Others were borderline cases.
example.tran: 一些明显不合适，可以马上排除。另一些则勉强合格。

value.tran: 勉强可以的；刚刚够格的
